         <abstract>
            <p>Characterisations of optimal linear estimation rules are given in terms of the reproducing kernel function of a suitable Hilbert space. The results are illustrated by means of three different, useful function spaces, showing, among other things, how Gaussian quadrature rules, and the Whittaker Cardinal Function, relate to optimal linear estimation rules in particular spaces.</p>
          </abstract>
